HEADWORD: Noisy
<hw>Nois"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Noisier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Noisiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From <er>Noise</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Making a noise, esp. a loud sound; clamorous;
vociferous; turbulent; boisterous; <as>as, the <ex>noisy</ex>
crowd</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of noise.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>noisy</xex>
town.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nolde</ent>⟦br⟧
